Description: Oval-shaped seal in dark quartz (?); underside engraved with a winged draped figure running to the left; complete.
Curator's comments: Rather similar Persian designs decorated seal impressions discovered in the Palace of Apries in Memphis. They are dated to the Persian Period. Such seals were related to the Persian administration or Persian officials. Petrie, W.M.F. 1909, The Palace of Apries. Memphis II, British School of Archaeology in Egypt 17, London, pl. XV. Petrie, W.M.F. 1910, Meydum and Memphis III, British School of Archaeology in Egypt 18, London, pl. XXXVI, 22-39.
Bibliographic references: Gem / Catalogue of Engraved Gems & Cameos, Greek, Etruscan & Roman in the British Museum (488)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (PA.19)
